{"title_page": "Waseda University Honjo Senior High School", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n|name           = Waseda University Honjo Senior High School\n|image          = <!-- Commented out: [[File:Waseda University Logo.svg|200px]] -->\n|native_name    = \u65e9\u7a32\u7530\u5927\u5b66\u672c\u5e84\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u9662\n|motto          = ''\u5b66\u554f\u306e\u72ec\u7acb''<br />(Independence of Learning)\n|established    = 1982\n|type           = [[Private High School|Private]]\n|endowment      = N/A\n|president      = Shigeru Yoshida\n|city           = [[Honjo, Saitama|Honjo]]\n|state          = [[Saitama Prefecture|Saitama]]\n|country        = [[Japan]]\n|students       = ~1,000\n|staff          =  \n|campus         = [[suburban area|suburban]]\n|colors         = Maroon {{Color box|maroon|border=darkgray}} [http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/adv/wol/dy/news/news03.htm]\n|free_label     = Athletics\n|affiliations   = Super Science High School\n|mascot         = Waseda Bear\n\n|website        = [http://waseda-honjo.jp Waseda University Honjo Senior High School]\n|footnotes      = \n|address        = 239-3 Kurisaki Honjo Saitama 367-0032 JAPAN\n|coor           = {{Coord|36|12|54.3|N|139|10|34.4|E|region:JP_type:edu_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}}\n|logo           = \n}}\n[[File:Wuhhs08.jpg|thumb|Waseda University Honjo Senior High School]]\n{{nihongo|'''Waseda University Honjo Senior High School'''|\u65e9\u7a32\u7530\u5927\u5b66\u672c\u5e84\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u9662|Waseda Daigaku Honjo K\u014dt\u014d Gakuin}} is a senior high school in Japan, located in [[Saitama Prefecture]]. It was founded in 1982 as a high school attached to [[Waseda University]]. Its motto is {{nihongo|\"independence of learning\"|\u5b66\u554f\u306e\u72ec\u7acb|gakumon-no-dokuritsu}}, which is the same motto as for Waseda University.\n\n==History==\nThe school was founded in April 1982 as a \"100th anniversary memorial project of Waseda University\". The school was founded as a boys' school, but it converted to a coeducational school in April 2007.\n\n==Present==\nThe school has continued interactions with prestige high schools as below.\n*[[Affiliated High School of Peking University]] \uff08{{CHN}}\uff09\n*[[National Taichung First Senior High School]] \uff08{{TWN}}\uff09\n*[[National Junior College]] \uff08{{SGP}}\uff09\n*[[Anyang Foreign Language High School]] \uff08{{KOR}}\uff09\n*[[SMA Negeri 2 Yogyakarta]] \uff08{{IDN}}\uff09\n\nAccording to the Hensachi (the indication showing the entrance difficulties by prep schools) rankings published by Sundai-Yobiko \uff08\u99ff\u53f0\u4e88\u5099\u6821\uff09, the school is one of the most selective senior high schools in Japan. Its entrance difficulty is usually considered as the top ranked among senior high schools in Saitama Prefacture.<ref>2009\u5168\u56fd\u4e3b\u8981\u79c1\u7acb180\u6821\u99ff\u53f0\u6700\u65b0\u504f\u5dee\u5024\uff08\u30b5\u30f3\u30c7\u30fc\u6bce\u65e52008.5.28\u53f7\uff09</ref>\n\n==Location/facility==\n\nThe closest station is the [[Honj\u014d-Waseda Station]].\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Gyochi Yoshida]] - [[Conductor (music)|Conductor]] of [[Nagoya Philharmonic Orchestra]]\n*Yoshio Tezuka - Special Advisor to the Prime Minister([[Yoshihiko Noda|Noda cabinet]])\n*[[Masafumi Kawaguchi]] -  [[American football]] player\n\n==Related books==\n* \u65e9\u7a32\u7530\u5927\u5b66\u672c\u5e84\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u9662\u7de8\u300e\u4e8c\u5341\u4e94\u5468\u5e74\u8a18\u5ff5\u8a8c : \u7d99\u627f\u3068\u767a\u5c55\u300f(Japanese), published in 2007\n* \u65e9\u7a32\u7530\u5927\u5b66\u672c\u5e84\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u9662\u7de8\u300e\u4e09\u5341\u5468\u5e74\u8a18\u5ff5\u8a8c\u300f(Japanese), published in 2012\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Japan|Schools}}\n* [http://waseda-honjo.jp Waseda University Honjo Senior High School]\n{{Waseda University}}\n{{authority control}}\n[[Category:High schools in Japan]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1982]]\n[[Category:Private schools in Japan]]\n[[Category:Waseda University]]\n[[Category:1982 establishments in Japan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n|name           = Waseda University Honjo Senior High School\n|image          = <!-- Commented out: [[File:Waseda University Logo.svg|200px]] -->\n|native_name    = \u65e9\u7a32\u7530\u5927\u5b66\u672c\u5e84\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u9662\n|motto          = ''\u5b66\u554f\u306e\u72ec\u7acb''<br />(Independence of Learning)\n|established    = 1982\n|type           = [[Private High School|Private]]\n|endowment      = N/A\n|president      = Shigeru Yoshida\n|city           = [[Honjo, Saitama|Honjo]]\n|state          = [[Saitama Prefecture|Saitama]]\n|country        = [[Japan]]\n|students       = ~1,000\n|staff          =  \n|campus         = [[suburban area|suburban]]\n|colors         = Maroon {{Color box|maroon|border=darkgray}} [http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/adv/wol/dy/news/news03.htm]\n|free_label     = Athletics\n|affiliations   = Super Science High School\n|mascot         = Waseda Bear\n\n|website        = [http://waseda-honjo.jp Waseda University Honjo Senior High School]\n|footnotes      = \n|address        = 239-3 Kurisaki Honjo Saitama 367-0032 JAPAN\n|coor           = {{Coord|36|12|54.3|N|139|10|34.4|E|region:JP_type:edu_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}}\n|logo           = \n}}\n[[File:Wuhhs08.jpg|thumb|Waseda University Honjo Senior High School]]\n{{nihongo|'''Waseda University Honjo Senior High School'''|\u65e9\u7a32\u7530\u5927\u5b66\u672c\u5e84\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u9662|Waseda Daigaku Honjo K\u014dt\u014d Gakuin}} is a senior high school in Japan, located in [[Saitama Prefecture]]. It was founded in 1982 as a high school attached to [[Waseda University]]. Its motto is {{nihongo|\"independence of learning\"|\u5b66\u554f\u306e\u72ec\u7acb|gakumon-no-dokuritsu}}, which is the same motto as for Waseda University.\n\n==History==\nThe school was founded in April 1982 as a \"100th anniversary memorial project of Waseda University\". The school was founded as a boys' school, but it converted to a coeducational school in April 2007.\n\n==Present==\nThe school has continued interactions with prestige high schools as below.\n*[[Affiliated High School of Peking University]] \uff08{{CHN}}\uff09\n*[[National Taichung First Senior High School]] \uff08{{TWN}}\uff09\n*[[National Junior College]] \uff08{{SGP}}\uff09\n*[[Anyang Foreign Language High School]] \uff08{{KOR}}\uff09\n*[[SMA Negeri 2 Yogyakarta]] \uff08{{IDN}}\uff09\n\nAccording to the Hensachi (the indication showing the entrance difficulties by prep schools) rankings published by Sundai-Yobiko \uff08\u99ff\u53f0\u4e88\u5099\u6821\uff09, the school is one of the most selective senior high schools in Japan. Its entrance difficulty is usually considered as the top ranked among senior high schools in Saitama Prefacture.<ref>2009\u5168\u56fd\u4e3b\u8981\u79c1\u7acb180\u6821\u99ff\u53f0\u6700\u65b0\u504f\u5dee\u5024\uff08\u30b5\u30f3\u30c7\u30fc\u6bce\u65e52008.5.28\u53f7\uff09</ref>\n\n==Location/facility==\n\n{{Empty section|date=February 2015}}\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Gyochi Yoshida]] - [[Conductor (music)|Conductor]] of [[Nagoya Philharmonic Orchestra]]\n*Yoshio Tezuka - Special Advisor to the Prime Minister([[Yoshihiko Noda|Noda cabinet]])\n*[[Masafumi Kawaguchi]] -  [[American football]] player\n\n==Related books==\n* \u65e9\u7a32\u7530\u5927\u5b66\u672c\u5e84\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u9662\u7de8\u300e\u4e8c\u5341\u4e94\u5468\u5e74\u8a18\u5ff5\u8a8c : \u7d99\u627f\u3068\u767a\u5c55\u300f(Japanese), published in 2007\n* \u65e9\u7a32\u7530\u5927\u5b66\u672c\u5e84\u9ad8\u7b49\u5b66\u9662\u7de8\u300e\u4e09\u5341\u5468\u5e74\u8a18\u5ff5\u8a8c\u300f(Japanese), published in 2012\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Japan|Schools}}\n* [http://waseda-honjo.jp Waseda University Honjo Senior High School]\n{{Waseda University}}\n{{authority control}}\n[[Category:High schools in Japan]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1